Fingerlingâ€¦rocks? I spotted these odd shapes while I was exploring. They likely formed billions of years ago when groundwater moved through, leaving minerals behind. In a less literal sense, my science team is interested in these rocks as a â€œdoorâ€ to the ancient past. As I climb up this mountain, Iâ€™m seeing higher levels of clay give way to salty minerals called sulfates â€“ clues as to how water dried up on Mars billions of years ago.
